<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114A/222</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-11T19:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 11, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3106. For <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">Garrett</persName>:</p>
                        <p>Your unnumbered [<hi rend="italic">14</hi>] October 5, 2 p.m. This
                            Government cannot accept the German proposal with regard to the
                            internment or deportation of German civilians in China as stated in your
                            telegram. While this Government does not view with favor the wholesale
                            internment or deportation of Germans residing in China, it desires to
                            remain free to support the same measure of control to be exercised over
                            German civilians in China as the Government of the United States
                            exercises over German civilians in this country.</p>
                        <p>Your action in refusing to see Mensing privately is approved.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>